        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Overall, the problems described in older issues tend to focus on foundational software engineering challenges such as maintenance and fault management, while more recent issues emphasize quality, testing, usability, and adoption of best practices and new technologies.",
        "citations": []
