[
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Prescriptive process models are prescriptions for the way software development should progress, outlining how the process is intended to be performed.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Some are prescriptions for the way software development should progress",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Descriptive process models, on the other hand, are descriptions of the way software development is done in actuality, reflecting the real practices used.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "and others are descriptions of the way software development is done in actuality",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "The purpose of prescriptive models is to guide the development process towards an ideal or intended method, ensuring consistency and quality.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Some are prescriptions for the way software development should progress",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "The purpose of descriptive models is to understand and document the actual process being used, which helps identify gaps between intended and actual practices.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Building a process model and discussing its subprocesses help the team understand the gap between what should be and what is.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "It is appropriate to use prescriptive models when the goal is to establish a consistent, repeatable process that meets quality and schedule goals.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "The model should reflect the goals of development, such as building high-quality software, finding faults early in development, and meeting required budget and schedule constraints.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
