        ],
        "type": null
    },
    {
        "role": "sentence",
        "segment": "A disadvantage is not explicitly stated, but it can be inferred that NSS might not capture all aspects of system size beyond use case scenarios.",
        "citations": [],
        "type": null
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Another size measure is the number of objects and methods used as a basic size measure in effort estimation, as used by Pfleeger (1991).",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Pfleeger (1991) used objects and methods as a basic size measure in her effort-estimation approach; she found that her method was more accurate than COCOMO in predicting the resulting effort needed to build several OO systems.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ],
        "type": null
    },
    {
