[
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "An example of black-box reuse from a previous programming project could be using routines from mathematical libraries or building graphical interfaces from predefined sets of components without modifying them.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "We perform black-box reuse often, when we use routines from mathematical libraries or build graphical interfaces from predefined sets of components.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Some benefits of black-box reuse include increased productivity and reduced cost, as it allows the reuse of existing components without modification, saving development time and effort.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Software researchers believe that reuse has great potential for increasing productivity and reducing cost, and some efforts to apply reuse technology confirm their belief.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "However, a drawback of black-box reuse is the challenge of verifying that a reused module performs its required function in an acceptable way, ensuring it is failure-free or thoroughly exercises the intended function.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "An important issue in black-box reuse is our ability to verify that a reused module performs its required function in an acceptable way. If the component is code, we want to be sure it is failure-free; if it is a test set, we want to be sure it thoroughly exercises the function for which it is intended.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "An example of a system for which black-box reuse would not have been appropriate is one that requires modification of components to fit particular needs, where clear-box reuse is necessary instead.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "As consumers, we can either use a product whole, without modification (called black-box reuse), or modify it to fit our particular needs (called clear-box reuse).",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    }
]

