[
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "According to the Belady-Lehman equation, the total maintenance effort M is given by M = p + K c - d, where p represents wholly productive efforts, c is complexity caused by lack of structured design and documentation, d is the degree to which the maintenance team is familiar with the software, and K is an empirical constant determined by the environment.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Belady and Lehman capture these effects in an equation: M = p + K c -d M is the total maintenance effort expended for a system, and p represents wholly productive efforts: analysis, evaluation, design, coding, and testing. c is complexity caused by the lack of structured design and documentation; it is reduced by d , the degree to which the maintenance team is familiar with the software. Finally, K is a constant determined by comparing this model with the effort relationships on actual projects; it is called an empirical constant because its value depends on the environment.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ],
        "type": null
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "If the development team is equally familiar with two systems (same d) and the systems are equally complex (same c), but the systems come from different environments, the expected maintenance effort is not necessarily equal because the empirical constant K depends on the environment.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Finally, K is a constant determined by comparing this model with the effort relationships on actual projects; it is called an empirical constant because its value depends on the environment.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ],
        "type": null
    },
    {
        "role": "sentence",
        "segment": "Therefore, all else being equal, if the development team is equally familiar with two systems from different environments, and the systems are equally complex, the expected maintenance effort is not necessarily roughly equal.",
        "citations": [],
        "type": null
    },
    {
        "role": "sentence",
        "segment": "Hence, the expectation stated in the question is FALSE.",
        "citations": [],
        "type": null
    }
]

