[
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "The slack time for an activity is calculated as the difference between the latest start time and the earliest start time for that activity.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Slack time = latest start time -earliest start time",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "From the activity graph, the activity starting at milestone F takes 2 days and leads to milestone H.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "img",
                "content": null,
                "img_id": "img0_se_theory_practice.pdf__chunk_None_846_205"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "To find the slack time for the activity starting at milestone F, we need to determine the earliest and latest start times for this activity.",
        "citations": []
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "The earliest start time for the activity at F is the earliest time to reach F, which is the sum of durations along the path A-B-D-F: 7 (A to B) + 2 (B to D) + 6 (D to F) = 15 days.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "img",
                "content": null,
                "img_id": "img0_se_theory_practice.pdf__chunk_None_846_205"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "The latest start time for the activity at F is the latest time it can start without delaying the project. The critical path is A-C-E-G-J-K with durations 5 + 3 + 10 + 10 + 5 = 33 days, so the project duration is 33 days.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "img",
                "content": null,
                "img_id": "img0_se_theory_practice.pdf__chunk_None_846_205"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "The latest start time for F is the latest time to reach F without delaying the project. Since F leads to H (2 days), H leads to I (1 day), I leads to K (10 days), the total duration from F to K is 2 + 1 + 10 = 13 days.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "img",
                "content": null,
                "img_id": "img0_se_theory_practice.pdf__chunk_None_846_205"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Therefore, the latest start time for F is the project duration minus the duration from F to K: 33 - 13 = 20 days.",
        "citations": []
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "The slack time for the activity starting at milestone F is the latest start time minus the earliest start time: 20 - 15 = 5 days.",
        "citations": []
    },
    {
        "role": "sentence",
        "segment": "The correct answer is b. 5",
        "citations": []
    }
]

